verbose_text: Although O 3 showed large increases during CNY due to the reductions in NO x and VOCs, we found that O x (=O 3 + NO 2), a more conserved tracer for photochemical processing, was decreased by 0.9-25.6% across the different PM levels, suggesting that the atmospheric oxidation capacity in winter using O x as a tracer may have uncertainties due to the much higher NO 2 than O 3.
